.progressLineardemoBasicUsage(
  ng-controller='ProgressLinearCtrl as vm'
  layout='column'
  layout-margin=''
  style={'padding': '25px'}
  ng-cloak=''
)
  h2.md-title Determinate
  p.
    For operations where the percentage of the operation completed can be determined,
    use a <b>determinate</b> indicator.  They give users a quick sense of how long an operation wil take.
  md-progress-linear(md-mode='determinate' value='{{vm.determinateValue}}')

  h4.md-title Indeterminate
  p.
    For operations where the user is asked to wait a moment while something finishes up,
    and it's not necessary to expose what's happening behind the scenes and how long it will take,
    use an <b>indeterminate</b> indicator:
  md-progress-linear(md-mode='indeterminate')

  h4.md-title Buffer
  p.
    For operations where the user wants to indicate some activity or loading from the server,
    use the <b>buffer</b> indicator:
  md-progress-linear.md-warn(
    md-mode='{{vm.modes[0]}}'
    value='{{vm.determinateValue}}'
    md-buffer-value='{{vm.determinateValue2}}'
  )

  h4.md-title Query
  p.
    For situations where the user wants to indicate pre-loading (until the loading can actually be made),
    use the <b>query</b> indicator:

  .container(ng-class="{'visible': !vm.activated}")
    md-progress-linear(md-mode='{{vm.modes[1]}}')
    .bottom-block
      span Loading application libraries...

  hr(ng-class="{'visible': vm.activated}")

  #loaders(layout='row' layout-align='start center')
    p Query and Buffer progress linear indicators:

    h5 Off
    md-switch(ng-model='vm.activated' ng-change='vm.toggleActivation()' aria-label="Enable Indicators")
    h5 On

  p.small.
    Note: With the above switch -- which simply clears the md-mode in each
    <code>&lt;md-progress-linear md-mode=""&gt;</code>
    element -- developers now easily disable the animations and hide their progress indicators.